==<span style="font-family:Grotesk; color:#F5F195; text-shadow: 0 0 10px #d4af37">'''''Overview'''''</span>==

'''Level 905''' is a level in which the past, the present, and the future can be viewed. All three each have their own unique sections, with each one representing one's past, present, and future; This can also extend to someone close to them. Each section will slowly transition on an hourly basis; The odds are 50/50 on which section it will be. One will know the section they are in is transitioning when everything around them is fading away and/or everything goes blurry. Eventually everything will go black for around a minute, then a new section will fade in.

'''Level 905''' is affected by [[Phenomenon 15]], leading to one's self being the only one in their own variation of the level. Each wanderer has their own variations of '''Level 905''', and one's variation of the level is never the same in others. Depending on one's mental and physical state, '''Level 905''''s physical form will alter to their desired hallway distances, room sizes, etc. Although as time goes on, it will grow more towards what they do not want instead.

===<span style="font-family:Grotesk; color:#F5F195; text-shadow: 0 0 10px #d4af37">'''''The Past'''''</span>===

The Past is one of three sections of '''Level 905'''. It focuses both on one's past and other people close to one's past. In this section, there are rooms and hallways that consist of either one's own memories or memories to a person close to the wanderer in a physically manifested state. There will also be random memories occasionally, rumored to be one's own past lives. All of it will be initially pleasant for them, as the rooms and hallways that appear first will be from happy memories. As the hour passes and more hallways/rooms are gone through, it will get progressively worse to the point one's mental state will decline unless they manage to transition into another section, at point which their mental state will be restored back to normal.
{{Blurimage|file=Epoch.png|caption=First photo ever taken of Level 905. Shows a memory of someone alone in a locker room.|align=right}}
In each room, there will always be a random object connected to it. If a wanderer touches that object, a memory will replay in their mind. The length of the memory lasts around 3-5 minutes. If one is in a familiar room that they remember and touch the object, it will replay a memory of themselves very clearly. If the wanderer is in a room not familiar to them, it is another person's own scattered memory. If the wanderer finds the object in that room, it will replay a memory unknown to them previously. As is with progressing through rooms, these memories will become progressively worse every time.

There is a theory that there are connections between one's own memories, and their past lives. [[M.E.G.]] scientists have theorized that one can inherit the memories of their deceased relatives and that those memories are stored in the brain. It is theorized that when one dies, those memories can never be accessed again. But the scientists claim this level does something that opens those memories again, though how it is done is still not known.

===<span style="font-family:Grotesk; color:#F5F195; text-shadow: 0 0 10px #d4af37">'''''The Present'''''</span>===

The Present is one of the three sections in '''Level 905'''. It focuses both on one's present mind and what is going on everywhere else in present time. This section contains rooms and hallways that can either project the one's present thoughts or can broadcast a full physical manifestation of an area currently active somewhere else. The people present in either will be projected as white outlines, only capturing the outlines of their bodies, clothes and facial expressions.
{{Blurimage|file=Yet to be, and yet it is there..png|caption=Photo of a physically manifested room in the present section, photographer got married in that exact room a few years later after this photo was taken.|align=right}}
A majority of the manifested physical areas either have been or will hold significance to wanderers when they view them. Not all of the areas that are manifested however will have significance; But in that scenario, there will be people in that physically manifested area that have been or will be important to one's self. It is unknown however if the areas yet to be seen by one's self or people yet to be by the seen by them are good or bad omens.

===<span style="font-family:Grotesk; color:#F5F195; text-shadow: 0 0 10px #d4af37">'''''The Future'''''</span>===

The Future is one of the three sections in '''Level 905'''. It focuses both on the one's future and the futures of both people and places they have impacted. This section reconstructs entire areas the wanderer has been in, will be in, or areas that will be. It is random how far into the future it is, but the majority of time it takes place 20-25 years after the present date. It is possible to even go hundreds of years into the future, even after the wanderer has since passed away. Though there have only been three confirmed cases of one's self going 100+ years into the future in this section.

One can see how far into the future they are by checking a calendar inside a nearby building. If there are no buildings nearby, there will be a random calendar on the ground where one first appears upon the future section fading in. There will also be either a portrait inside of a building or a small statue outside of who has impacted that area. Majority of the time it will be the wanderer themselves, but it can also be a person they have met or will meet. Every 15-20 minutes, the area will reconfigure itself into a new different area. This happens 3-4 times before everything fades out and a new section fades in.

===<span style="font-family:Grotesk; color:#F5F195; text-shadow: 0 0 10px #d4af37">'''''The Clocks'''''</span>===
Throughout both the Past and Future sections of '''Level 905''', there will be very rarely a series of multiple clocks that appear on the walls. All of these clocks are set at different times, coinciding with active time zones in both the frontrooms and many levels in the backrooms. One of these clocks however can represent what time one was born and when hour they will die.

The one in the Past section will show the exact time the wanderer is born and will stay at that position until a transition happens. The one in the Future sections will not be static, and the only way to tell what the wanderer's death hour is to stand still for 30 minutes straight, looking at the clocks. After 30 minutes, one of the clocks will suddenly reverse direction at an intense speed. After a random amount of time, it will stop at a random time. That will be the wanderer's future time of death.


==<span style="font-family:Grotesk; color:#F5F195; text-shadow: 0 0 10px #d4af37">'''''Entities'''''</span>==

===<span style="font-family:Grotesk; color:#F5F195; text-shadow: 0 0 10px #d4af37">'''''The Outlines'''''</span>===

The Outlines are entities in '''Level 905''' that appear in all three sections. They are partial-physical manifestations of real people but only have glowing white outlines of their physical features, what they are wearing, and their facial expressions. How bright they glow upon looking at them is of how important they are to one's self or someone else they know, even if that someone else is someone they don't know very well; They were, are, or will be important to the wanderer. They can't be interacted with however, as they are part of a scripted vision no matter what section they are in.


==<span style="font-family:Grotesk; color:#F5F195; text-shadow: 0 0 10px #d4af37">'''''Groups and Organizations'''''</span>==

===<span style="font-family:Grotesk; color:#F5F195; text-shadow: 0 0 10px #d4af37">'''''The Enlighted Perspective Society'''''</span>===

The Enlightened Perspective Society, or T.E.R.P. for short, is a group of around 20-45 people who believe '''Level 905''' is the solution to everything. They each wear medieval clothing as they believe it makes them more "civilized" than other groups. The T.E.R.P. sends 3-5 members every day into '''Level 905''', and all of them explore all three sections for exactly 24 hours despite the mental hazard risks. They can all enter at the same time, yet they will each be sent into their own variations of '''Level 905''' due to [[Phenomenon 15]].
{{Blurimage|file=T.E.R.P Poster.png|caption=Recruiting Poster for the T.E.R.P, found in Level 11.|align=right}}
The T.E.R.P. members ask themselves three questions when they explore each section of '''Level 905'''. For The Past section, they ask themselves, "What did my past self do, and how does that relate to me now?" In The Present section, they all ask themselves, "What is going on all around me right now, and how does it translate to me?" In The Future section, they ask themselves, "How does this future happen, and should I change that future?" After 24 hours of going through all sections and asking themselves those questions in their minds over and over again, they leave the level and the next group enters.

After around 5-8 days, once each group has been sent to '''Level 905''', they all meet together in [[Level 11]] for a conference. At the conference, the leader will speak about why '''Level 905''' is the key to everything and how great it is. After the speech, all members will, one at a time, go up to the podium, introduce themselves, and describe what they saw during their 24 hours in '''Level 905'''. After all members have spoken, the leader will step up to the podium again and commence the 10-minute silent period. The silent period is when all members must think in silence about the answers to the three questions they asked themselves in '''Level 905'''.

After the 10 minutes are up, questions answered or not, the leader will give a brief thanks to every member and give another short speech on the importance of '''Level 905'''. After the brief speech is given, he will then commence the "lottery." He will select members at random, pair them up into groups of three to five people, and assign them a random day. After everyone has been assigned to their days and groups, the leader will give a brief ten minutes for all members to get into their assigned groups and introduce themselves. After the ten minutes are up, the leader will then finally end the conference.

If one wants to join the group, they must meet the leader in person and meet certain criteria. They must first prove they are not part of any other groups like the [[M.E.G.]] They must also prove that they have visited '''Level 905''' on their own before. Finally, if they meet those criteria, they must take an "Enlightened Philosophy" class taught by the leader himself. After all criteria have been met, they will officially become a member of T.E.R.P. If one leaves T.E.R.P., they are free to do so. But they are not allowed to become a member anymore if they leave.

==<span style="font-family:Grotesk; color:#F5F195; text-shadow: 0 0 10px #d4af37">'''''Entrances and Exits'''''</span>==

===<span style="font-family:Grotesk; color:#F5F195; text-shadow: 0 0 10px #d4af37">'''''Entrances'''''</span>===

In [[Level 986]], if finds a sign reading "Answers" and follow it, it will lead here.

In [[Level 570]], if one finds a yellow colored cleaning product with a sun on it, pick it up and chant the words "Take me to the land of life", they will be brought here.

In [[Level 168]], if one finds a glowing yellow staircase that leads upstairs, go up the staircase and it will lead here.

In [[Level 634]], if one finds a snow sculpture of a clock and falls asleep next to it, they will wake-up here. 

===<span style="font-family:Grotesk; color:#F5F195; text-shadow: 0 0 10px #d4af37">'''''Exits'''''</span>===

After 24 hours of being in the level, if one is in the past section, a wooden white door will appear. Go through it and it will lead to [[Level 760]].

If one finds an out-of-place statue of themselves in the future section and touches it, they will be brought to [[Level 634]].


